Hi. We are struggling with using path planner to have our robot to follow a path in autonomous mode. When we try to make the robot follow a straight path (with no rotating the robot) the robot begins to move in the opposite direction than what it should be going and then starts to rotate violently. We’ve attached our code from github.

Your SwerveSubsystem’s Rotation2ds are the wrong way around:

github.com

Team4169/Swerve2024/blob/40e40883bba919d09f87fb3ae4b9e23cacd895df/subsystems/swervesubsystem.py#L103-L108


      
    
          
  1. def getHeading(self):
    2. 
          
  2.     return  math.remainder(self.gyro.getAngle(), 360)
    3. 
          
  3.     
    4. 
          
  4. 
          
  5. def getRotation2d(self) -> Rotation2d:
    6. 
          
  6.     return Rotation2d.fromDegrees(self.getHeading())
    7.

Use self.gyro.getRotation2d so positive is the correct direction for the right hand coordinate system.
